grades.title: 1922P20
grades.summary: Density 919 kg/m3, MFR (2.16 kg) 22 g/10 min
grades.description:
SABIC® LDPE Powder 1922P20 is an additive free CTR® tubular grade with a typically high purity and as such a fine material for masterbatches in film applications.

Application
SABIC® LDPE Powder 1922P20 is a normal sized powder grade. Since the grade is supplied in powder form it is typically used for pre mixing. The flow and dispersion of pigments and additives that tend towards blocking are typically improved by adding this grade.

This product is not intended for and must not be used in any pharmaceutical/medical applications.

grades.title: 1922P3
grades.summary: Density 919 kg/m3, MFR (2.16 kg) 22 g/10 min
grades.description:
SABIC® LDPE Powder 1922P3 is an additive free CTR® tubular grade with a typically high purity. The grade is supplied in powder form. 

Application 
SABIC® LDPE Powder 1922P3 is typically used for textile coating, carpet backing and compounding applications. The very fine particle size makes that this grade is typically used for delicate tissues in textile coating. For compounding typically fine incorporation in mixtures or blends is possible. The enhanced MFR provides a low zero shear viscosity or good flow in extrusion processes. 

This product is not intended for and must not be used in any pharmaceutical/medical applications.

grades.title: 1965P5
grades.summary: Density 919 kg/m3, MFR (2.16 kg) 65 g/10 min
grades.description:
SABIC® LDPE Powder 1965P5 is an additive free standard CTR® tubular grade with a high melt flow rate and is known for its typically high filler/pigments acceptance properties. This grade is supplied in powder form.

Application
SABIC® LDPE Powder 1965P5 is a medium sized powder grade with a low viscosity for textile coating, carpet backing and compounding applications. It is further used for masterbatches with a typically very high loading of carbon black, titanium dioxide or pigment.

This product is not intended for and must not be used in any pharmaceutical/medical applications.

grades.title: 2102P5
grades.summary: Density 921 kg/m3, MFR (2.16 kg) 1.9 g/10 min
grades.description:
SABIC® LDPE Powder 2102P5 is an additive free standard CTR® tubular grade for masterbatch with a relatively low melt flow rate. This grade is supplied in powder form.

Application
SABIC® LDPE Powder 2102P5 is a general medium sized powder grade, typical used for textile coating, carpet backing and compounding applications with a low viscosity. Further it can be used for low filled or additive masterbatches (e.g. slip agents, anti fog agents, anti static agents, thermal stabilizers).

This product is not intended for and must not be used in any pharmaceutical/medical applications.
